        <h2>The bottom line</h2>
        <p>Contractor Foreman is a legitimate construction management platform that delivers real value, especially for budget-conscious contractors. The UI is showing its age, and support could be better — but if the price point is the deciding factor, it beats its nearest competitors at every tier. Don't count it out just because it costs less than everyone else.</p>

        <h2>Frequently asked questions</h2>

        <h3>Is Contractor Foreman cloud-based?</h3>
        <p>Yes, it's fully cloud-based with web and mobile apps. No local software installation required.</p>

        <h3>Does Contractor Foreman work for commercial contractors?</h3>
        <p>It can be used for commercial work, but it lacks the enterprise compliance features (submittals, RFI management, certified payroll) that commercial GCs typically need. For basic commercial project management, it's workable; for complex commercial projects, Procore is the better fit.</p>

        <h3>How does Contractor Foreman compare to JobTread?</h3>
        <p>Contractor Foreman is cheaper and has more feature breadth; JobTread has a better interface and better estimating workflow. For a solo contractor watching costs, Contractor Foreman wins on price. For a team that prioritizes usability and will grow, JobTread is often the better long-term platform.</p>

